    Flowable Process REST API v1

    Scroll down for code samples, example requests and responses. Select a language for code samples from the tabs above or the mobile navigation menu.

    Flowable REST principles

    Installation and Authentication

    Flowable includes a REST API to the Flowable engine that can be installed by deploying the flowable-rest.war file to a servlet container like Apache Tomcat. However, it can also be used in another web-application by including the servlet and its mapping in your application and add all flowable-rest dependencies to the classpath.

    By default the Flowable engine will connect to an in-memory H2 database. You can change the database settings in the db.properties file in the WEB-INF/classes folder. The REST API uses JSON format (http://www.json.org) and is built upon the Spring MVC (http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/spring-framework-reference/html/mvc.html).

    All REST-resources require a valid Flowable-user to be authenticated by default. Basic HTTP access authentication is used, so you should always include a Authorization: Basic ...== HTTP-header when performing requests or include the username and password in the request-url (for example, http://username:password@localhost:8080/xyz).

    We recommend that you use Basic Authentication in combination with HTTPS.

    Configuration

    The Flowable REST web application uses Spring Java Configuration for starting the Flowable Form engine, defining the basic authentication security using Spring security, and to define the variable converters for specific variable handling. A small number of properties can be defined by changing the engine.properties file you can find in the WEB-INF/classes folder. If you need more advanced configuration options there's the possibility to override the default Spring beans in XML in the flowable-custom-context.xml file you can also find in the WEB-INF/classes folder. An example configuration is already in comments in this file. This is also the place to override the default RestResponseFactory by defining a new Spring bean with the name restResponsefactory and use your custom implementation class for it.

    Usage in Tomcat

    Due to default security properties on Tomcat, escaped forward slashes (%2F and %5C) are not allowed by default (400-result is returned). This may have an impact on the deployment resources and their data-URL, as the URL can potentially contain escaped forward slashes.

    When issues are experienced with unexpected 400-results, set the following system-property:

    -Dorg.apache.tomcat.util.buf.UDecoder.ALLOW_ENCODED_SLASH=true

    It's best practice to always set the Accept and Content-Type (in case of posting/putting JSON) headers to application/json on the HTTP requests described below.

    Methods and return-codes

    HTTP-methods and corresponding operations

    Method Operations
    GET Get a single resource or get a collection of resources.
    POST Create a new resource. Also used for executing resource-queries which have a too complex request-structure to fit in the query-URL of a GET-request.
    PUT Update properties of an existing resource. Also used for invoking actions on an existing resource.
    DELETE Delete an existing resource.

    HTTP-methods response codes

    Response Description
    200 - Ok The operation was successful and a response has been returned (GET and PUT requests).
    201 - Created The operation was successful and the entity has been created and is returned in the response-body (POST request).
    204 - No content The operation was successful and entity has been deleted and therefore there is no response-body returned (DELETE request).
    401 - Unauthorized The operation failed. The operation requires an Authentication header to be set. If this was present in the request, the supplied credentials are not valid or the user is not authorized to perform this operation.
    403 - Forbidden The operation is forbidden and should not be re-attempted. This implies an issue with authorization not authentication, it's an operation that is not allowed. Example: deleting a task that is part of a running process is not allowed and will never be allowed, regardless of the user or process/task state.
    404 - Not found The operation failed. The requested resource was not found.
    405 - Method not allowed The operation failed. The method is not allowed for this resource. For example, trying to update (PUT) a deployment-resource will result in a 405 status.
    409 - Conflict The operation failed. The operation causes an update of a resource that has been updated by another operation, which makes the update no longer valid. Can also indicate a resource that is being created in a collection where a resource with that identifier already exists.
    415 - Unsupported Media Type The operation failed. The request body contains an unsupported media type. Also occurs when the request-body JSON contains an unknown attribute or value that doesn't have the right format/type to be accepted.
    500 - Internal server error The operation failed. An unexpected exception occurred while executing the operation. The response-body contains details about the error.

    The media-type of the HTTP-responses is always application/json unless binary content is requested (for example, deployment resource data), the media-type of the content is used.

    Error response body

    When an error occurs (both client and server, 4XX and 5XX status-codes) the response body contains an object describing the error that occurred. An example for a 404-status when a task is not found:

    {
  "statusCode" : 404,
  "errorMessage" : "Could not find a task with id '444'."
}

    Request parameters

    URL fragments

    Parameters that are part of the URL (for example, the deploymentId parameter in http://host/flowable-rest/form-api/form-repository/deployments/{deploymentId}) need to be properly escaped (see link URL-encoding or Percent-encoding) in case the segment contains special characters. Most frameworks have this functionality built in, but it should be taken into account. Especially for segments that can contain forward-slashes (for example, deployment resource), this is required.

    Rest URL query parameters

    Parameters added as query-string in the URL (for example, the name parameter used in http://host/flowable-rest/form-api/form-repository/deployments?name=Deployment) can have the following types and are mentioned in the corresponding REST-API documentation:

    Type Format
    String Plain text parameters. Can contain any valid characters that are allowed in URLs. In the case of a XXXLike parameter, the string should contain the wildcard character % (properly URL-encoded). This allows you to specify the intent of the like-search. For example, 'Tas%' matches all values, starting with 'Tas'.
    Integer Parameter representing an integer value. Can only contain numeric non-decimal values, between -2.147.483.648 and 2.147.483.647.
    Long Parameter representing a long value. Can only contain numeric non-decimal values, between -9.223.372.036.854.775.808 and 9.223.372.036.854.775.807.
    Boolean Parameter representing a boolean value. Can be either true or false. All other values other than these will cause a '405 - Bad request' response.
    Date Parameter representing a date value. Use the ISO-8601 date-format (see ISO-8601 on wikipedia using both time and date-components (e.g. 2013-04-03T23:45Z).

    JSON body parameters

    Type Format
    String Plain text parameters. In the case of a XXXLike parameter, the string should contain the wildcard character %. This allows you to specify the intent of the like-search. For example, 'Tas%' matches all values, starting with 'Tas'.
    Integer Parameter representing an integer value, using a JSON number. Can only contain numeric non-decimal values, between -2.147.483.648 and 2.147.483.647.
    Long Parameter representing a long value, using a JSON number. Can only contain numeric non-decimal values, between -9.223.372.036.854.775.808 and 9.223.372.036.854.775.807.
    Date Parameter representing a date value, using a JSON text. Use the ISO-8601 date-format (see ISO-8601 on wikipedia using both time and date-components (for example, 2013-04-03T23:45Z).

    Paging and sorting

    Paging and order parameters can be added as query-string in the URL (for example, the name parameter used in http://host/flowable-rest/form-api/form-repository/deployments?sort=name).

    Parameter Default value Description
    sort different per query implementation Name of the sort key, for which the default value and the allowed values are different per query implementation.
    order asc Sorting order which can be 'asc' or 'desc'.
    start 0 Parameter to allow for paging of the result. By default the result will start at 0.
    size 10 Parameter to allow for paging of the result. By default the size will be 10.

    JSON query variable format

    {
  "name" : "variableName",
  "value" : "variableValue",
  "operation" : "equals",
  "type" : "string"
}

    Variable query JSON parameters

    Parameter Required Description
    name No Name of the variable to include in a query. Can be empty in the case where 'equals' is used in some queries to query for resources that have any variable name with the given value.
    value Yes Value of the variable included in the query, should include a correct format for the given type.
    operator Yes Operator to use in query, can have the following values: equals, notEquals, equalsIgnoreCase, notEqualsIgnoreCase, lessThan, greaterThan, lessThanOrEquals, greaterThanOrEquals and like.
    type No Type of variable to use. When omitted, the type will be deduced from the value parameter. Any JSON text-values will be considered of type string, JSON booleans of type boolean, JSON numbers of type long or integer depending on the size of the number. We recommended you include an explicit type when in doubt. Types supported out of the box are listed below.

    Default query JSON types

    Type name Description
    string Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.String.
    short Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.Integer.
    integer Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.Integer.
    long Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.Long.
    double Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.Double.
    boolean Value is treated as and converted to a java.lang.Boolean.
    date Value is treated as and converted to a java.util.Date. The JSON string will be converted using ISO-8601 date format.

    Variable representation

    When working with variables (execute decision), the REST API uses some common principles and JSON-format for both reading and writing. The JSON representation of a variable looks like this:

    {
  "name" : "variableName",
  "value" : "variableValue",
  "valueUrl" : "http://...",
  "type" : "string"
}

    Variable JSON attributes

    Parameter Required Description
    name Yes Name of the variable.
    value No Value of the variable. When writing a variable and value is omitted, null will be used as value.
    valueUrl No When reading a variable of type binary or serializable, this attribute will point to the URL from where the raw binary data can be fetched.
    type No Type of the variable. See table below for additional information on types. When writing a variable and this value is omitted, the type will be deduced from the raw JSON-attribute request type and is limited to either string, double, integer and boolean. We advise you to always include a type to make sure no wrong assumption about the type are made.

    Variable Types

    Type name Description
    string Value is treated as a java.lang.String. Raw JSON-text value is used when writing a variable.
    integer Value is treated as a java.lang.Integer. When writing, JSON number value is used as base for conversion, falls back to JSON text.
    short Value is treated as a java.lang.Short. When writing, JSON number value is used as base for conversion, falls back to JSON text.
    long Value is treated as a java.lang.Long. When writing, JSON number value is used as base for conversion, falls back to JSON text.
    double Value is treated as a java.lang.Double. When writing, JSON number value is used as base for conversion, falls back to JSON text.
    boolean Value is treated as a java.lang.Boolean. When writing, JSON boolean value is used for conversion.
    date Value is treated as a java.util.Date. When writing, the JSON text will be converted using ISO-8601 date format.

    It's possible to support additional variable-types with a custom JSON representation (either simple value or complex/nested JSON object). By extending the initializeVariableConverters() method on org.flowable.rest.dmn.service.api.DmnRestResponseFactory, you can add additional **org.flowable.rest.variable.RestVariableConverter classes to support converting your POJOs to a format suitable for transferring through REST and converting the REST-value back to your POJO. The actual transformation to JSON is done by Jackson.

    Forms

    Get form data

    Code samples

    # You can also use wget
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data \
  -H 'Accept: application/json'


    GET http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080

Accept: application/json


    var headers = {
  'Accept':'application/json'

};

$.ajax({
  url: 'http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
  method: 'get',

  headers: headers,
  success: function(data) {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(data));
  }
})

    const request = require('node-fetch');

const headers = {
  'Accept':'application/json'

};

fetch('http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
{
  method: 'GET',

  headers: headers
})
.then(function(res) {
    return res.json();
}).then(function(body) {
    console.log(body);
});

    require 'rest-client'
require 'json'

headers = {
  'Accept' => 'application/json'
}

result = RestClient.get 'http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
  params: {
  }, headers: headers

p JSON.parse(result)

    import requests
headers = {
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

r = requests.get('http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data', params={

}, headers = headers)

print r.json()

    URL obj = new URL("http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data");
HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) obj.openConnection();
con.setRequestMethod("GET");
int responseCode = con.getResponseCode();
BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(
    new InputStreamReader(con.getInputStream()));
String inputLine;
StringBuffer response = new StringBuffer();
while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null) {
    response.append(inputLine);
}
in.close();
System.out.println(response.toString());

    GET /form/form-data

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    taskId query string false No description
    processDefinitionId query string false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "formKey": "null",
  "deploymentId": "2",
  "processDefinitionId": "3",
  "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definition/3",
  "taskId": "6",
  "taskUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/task/6",
  "formProperties": [
    {
      "id": "room",
      "name": "Room",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "string",
      "readable": true,
      "writable": true,
      "required": true,
      "datePattern": "string",
      "enumValues": [
        {
          "id": "normal",
          "name": "Normal bed"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates that form data could be queried. FormDataResponse
    404 Not Found Indicates that form data could not be found. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Submit task form data

    Code samples

    # You can also use wget
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'Accept: application/json'


    POST http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json


    var headers = {
  'Content-Type':'application/json',
  'Accept':'application/json'

};

$.ajax({
  url: 'http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
  method: 'post',

  headers: headers,
  success: function(data) {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(data));
  }
})

    const request = require('node-fetch');
const inputBody = '{
  "action": "string",
  "processDefinitionId": "string",
  "taskId": "string",
  "businessKey": "string",
  "properties": [
    {
      "id": "room",
      "name": "Room",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "string",
      "readable": true,
      "writable": true,
      "required": true,
      "datePattern": "string",
      "enumValues": [
        {
          "id": "normal",
          "name": "Normal bed"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}';
const headers = {
  'Content-Type':'application/json',
  'Accept':'application/json'

};

fetch('http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
{
  method: 'POST',
  body: inputBody,
  headers: headers
})
.then(function(res) {
    return res.json();
}).then(function(body) {
    console.log(body);
});

    require 'rest-client'
require 'json'

headers = {
  'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
  'Accept' => 'application/json'
}

result = RestClient.post 'http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/form/form-data',
  params: {
  }, headers: headers

p JSON.parse(result)

  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'

}, headers = headers)

print r.json()

    POST /form/form-data

    Body parameter

    [
  {
    "id": "room",
    "name": "Room",
    "type": "string",
    "value": "string",
    "readable": true,
    "writable": true,
    "required": true,
    "datePattern": "string",
    "enumValues": [
      {
        "id": "normal",
        "name": "Normal bed"
      }
    ]
  }
]

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    body body SubmitFormRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "187",
  "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
  "businessKey": "myBusinessKey",
  "suspended": true,
  "ended": true,
  "processDefinitionId": "oneTaskProcess:1:158",
  "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
  "activityId": "processTask",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "myVariable",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "test",
      "valueUrl": "http://....",
      "scope": "string"
    }
  ],
  "tenantId": "null",
  "completed": true
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates request was successful and the form data was submitted ProcessInstanceResponse
    204 No Content If TaskId has been provided, Indicates request was successful and the form data was submitted. Returns empty None
    400 Bad Request Indicates an parameter was passed in the wrong format. The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /history/historic-activity-instances

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    activityId query string false An id of the activity instance.
    activityInstanceId query string false An id of the historic activity instance.
    activityName query string false The name of the historic activity instance.
    activityType query string false The element type of the historic activity instance.
    executionId query string false The execution id of the historic activity instance.
    finished query boolean false Indication if the historic activity instance is finished.
    taskAssignee query string false The assignee of the historic activity instance.
    processInstanceId query string false The process instance id of the historic activity instance.
    processDefinitionId query string false The process definition id of the historic activity instance.
    tenantId query string false Only return instances with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return instances with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns instances without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.

    Example responses

    GET /history/historic-process-instances

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    processInstanceId query string false An id of the historic process instance.
    processDefinitionKey query string false The process definition key of the historic process instance.
    processDefinitionId query string false The process definition id of the historic process instance.
    businessKey query string false The business key of the historic process instance.
    involvedUser query string false An involved user of the historic process instance.
    finished query boolean false Indication if the historic process instance is finished.
    superProcessInstanceId query string false An optional parent process id of the historic process instance.
    excludeSubprocesses query boolean false Return only historic process instances which aren?t sub processes.
    finishedAfter query string(date-time) false Return only historic process instances that were finished after this date.
    finishedBefore query string(date-time) false Return only historic process instances that were finished before this date.
    startedAfter query string(date-time) false Return only historic process instances that were started after this date.
    startedBefore query string(date-time) false Return only historic process instances that were started before this date.
    startedBy query string false Return only historic process instances that were started by this user.
    includeProcessVariables query boolean false An indication if the historic process instance variables should be returned as well.
    tenantId query string false Only return instances with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return instances with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns instances without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    processInstanceId path string true No description
    body body CommentResponse false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "string",
  "author": "string",
  "message": "string",
  "time": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "taskId": "string",
  "taskUrl": "string",
  "processInstanceId": "string",
  "processInstanceUrl": "string"
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK successful operation CommentResponse
    201 Created Indicates the comment was created and the result is returned. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates the comment is missing from the request. None
    404 Not Found Indicates that the historic process instance could not be found. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /history/historic-process-instances/{processInstanceId}/variables/{variableName}/data

    The response body contains the binary value of the variable. When the variable is of type binary, the content-type of the response is set to application/octet-stream, regardless of the content of the variable or the request accept-type header. In case of serializable, application/x-java-serialized-object is used as content-type.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    processInstanceId path string true No description
    variableName path string true No description

    Example responses

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the process instance was found and the requested variable data is returned. Inline
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested process instance was not found or the process instance doesn?t have a variable with the given name or the variable doesn?t have a binary stream available. Status message provides additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /history/historic-task-instances

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    taskId query string false An id of the historic task instance.
    processInstanceId query string false The process instance id of the historic task instance.
    processDefinitionKey query string false The process definition key of the historic task instance.
    processDefinitionKeyLike query string false The process definition key of the historic task instance, which matches the given value.
    processDefinitionId query string false The process definition id of the historic task instance.
    processDefinitionName query string false The process definition name of the historic task instance.
    processDefinitionNameLike query string false The process definition name of the historic task instance, which matches the given value.
    processBusinessKey query string false The process instance business key of the historic task instance.
    processBusinessKeyLike query string false The process instance business key of the historic task instance that matches the given value.
    executionId query string false The execution id of the historic task instance.
    taskDefinitionKey query string false The task definition key for tasks part of a process
    taskName query string false The task name of the historic task instance.
    taskNameLike query string false The task name with like operator for the historic task instance.
    taskDescription query string false The task description of the historic task instance.
    taskDescriptionLike query string false The task description with like operator for the historic task instance.
    taskCategory query string false Select tasks with the given category. Note that this is the task category, not the category of the process definition (namespace within the BPMN Xml).
    taskDeleteReason query string false The task delete reason of the historic task instance.
    taskDeleteReasonLike query string false The task delete reason with like operator for the historic task instance.
    taskAssignee query string false The assignee of the historic task instance.
    taskAssigneeLike query string false The assignee with like operator for the historic task instance.
    taskOwner query string false The owner of the historic task instance.
    taskOwnerLike query string false The owner with like operator for the historic task instance.
    taskInvolvedUser query string false An involved user of the historic task instance
    taskPriority query string false The priority of the historic task instance.
    finished query boolean false Indication if the historic task instance is finished.
    processFinished query boolean false Indication if the process instance of the historic task instance is finished.
    parentTaskId query string false An optional parent task id of the historic task instance.
    dueDate query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have a due date equal this date.
    dueDateAfter query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have a due date after this date.
    dueDateBefore query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have a due date before this date.
    withoutDueDate query boolean false Return only historic task instances that have no due-date. When false is provided as value, this parameter is ignored.
    taskCompletedOn query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have been completed on this date.
    taskCompletedAfter query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have been completed after this date.
    taskCompletedBefore query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that have been completed before this date.
    taskCreatedOn query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that were created on this date.
    taskCreatedBefore query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that were created before this date.
    taskCreatedAfter query string(date-time) false Return only historic task instances that were created after this date.
    includeTaskLocalVariables query boolean false An indication if the historic task instance local variables should be returned as well.
    includeProcessVariables query boolean false An indication if the historic task instance global variables should be returned as well.
    tenantId query string false Only return historic task instances with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return historic task instances with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns historic task instances without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "processDefinitionId": "string",
      "processDefinitionUrl": "string",
      "processInstanceId": "string",
      "processInstanceUrl": "string",
      "executionId": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "description": "string",
      "deleteReason": "string",
      "owner": "string",
      "assignee": "string",
      "startTime": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
      "endTime": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
      "durationInMillis": 0,
      "workTimeInMillis": 0,
      "claimTime": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
      "taskDefinitionKey": "string",
      "formKey": "string",
      "priority": 0,
      "dueDate": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
      "parentTaskId": "string",
      "url": "string",
      "variables": [
        {
          "name": "myVariable",
          "type": "string",
          "value": "test",
          "valueUrl": "http://....",
          "scope": "string"
        }
      ],
      "tenantId": "string",
      "category": "string"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates that historic task instances could be queried. DataResponseHistoricTaskInstanceResponse
    404 Not Found Indicates an parameter was passed in the wrong format. The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /identity/groups

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return group with the given id
    name query string false Only return groups with the given name
    type query string false Only return groups with the given type
    nameLike query string false Only return groups with a name like the given value. Use % as wildcard-character.
    member query string false Only return groups which have a member with the given username.
    potentialStarter query string false Only return groups which members are potential starters for a process-definition with the given id.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort name
    sort type

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "testgroup",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/identity/groups/testgroup",
      "name": "Test group",
      "type": "Test type"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the requested groups were returned. DataResponseGroupResponse
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Parameters

    Status Meaning Description Schema

    201 Created Indicates the group was found and the member has been added. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates the userId was not included in the request body. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested group was not found. None
    409 Conflict Indicates the requested user is already a member of the group. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    URL obj = new URL("http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/identity/groups/{groupId}/members/{userId}");
HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) obj.openConnection();
con.setRequestMethod("DELETE");
int responseCode = con.getResponseCode();
BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(
    new InputStreamReader(con.getInputStream()));
String inputLine;
StringBuffer response = new StringBuffer();
while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null) {
    response.append(inputLine);
}
in.close();
System.out.println(response.toString());

    DELETE /identity/groups/{groupId}/members/{userId}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    groupId path string true No description
    userId path string true No description

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    204 No Content Indicates the group was found and the member has been deleted. The response body is left empty intentionally. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested group was not found or that the user is not a member of the group. The status description contains additional information about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /identity/users

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return group with the given id
    firstName query string false Only return users with the given firstname
    lastName query string false Only return users with the given lastname
    email query string false Only return users with the given email
    firstNameLike query string false Only return userswith a firstname like the given value. Use % as wildcard-character.
    lastNameLike query string false Only return users with a lastname like the given value. Use % as wildcard-character.
    emailLike query string false Only return users with an email like the given value. Use % as wildcard-character.
    memberOfGroup query string false Only return users which are a member of the given group.
    potentialStarter query string false Only return users which members are potential starters for a process-definition with the given id.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort firstName
    sort lastname
    sort email

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "testuser",
      "firstName": "Fred",
      "lastName": "Smith",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser",
      "email": "no-reply@flowable.org",
      "pictureUrl": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser/picture",
      "password": "string"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the group exists and is returned. DataResponseUserResponse
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    PUT /identity/users/{userId}

    All request values are optional. For example, you can only include the firstName attribute in the request body JSON-object, only updating the firstName of the user, leaving all other fields unaffected. When an attribute is explicitly included and is set to null, the user-value will be updated to null. Example: {"firstName" : null} will clear the firstName of the user).

    Body parameter

    {
  "id": "testuser",
  "firstName": "Fred",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "url": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser",
  "email": "no-reply@flowable.org",
  "pictureUrl": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser/picture",
  "password": "string"
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    userId path string true No description
    body body UserRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "testuser",
  "firstName": "Fred",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "url": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser",
  "email": "no-reply@flowable.org",
  "pictureUrl": "http://localhost:8182/identity/users/testuser/picture",
  "password": "string"
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the user was updated. UserResponse
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested user was not found. None
    409 Conflict Indicates the requested user was updated simultaneously. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Body parameter

  "key": "jobTitle",

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    userId path string true No description
    body body UserInfoRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "key": "jobTitle",
  "value": "Muppet",
  "url": "http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/identity/users/kermit/info/jobTitle"
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK successful operation UserInfoResponse
    201 Created Indicates the user was found and the info has been created. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates the key or value was missing from the request body. Status description contains additional information about the error. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested user was not found. None
    409 Conflict Indicates there is already an info-entry with the given key for the user, update the resource instance (PUT). None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

  "url": "http://localhost:8080/flowable-rest/service/identity/users/kermit/info/jobTitle"
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema

    404 Not Found Indicates the requested user was not found or the user doesn?t have info for the given key. Status description contains additional information about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /identity/users/{userId}/picture

    The response body contains the raw picture data, representing the user's picture. The Content-type of the response corresponds to the mimeType that was set when creating the picture.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    userId path string true No description

    Example responses

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the user was found and has a picture, which is returned in the body. Inline
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested user was not found or the user does not have a profile picture. Status-description contains additional information about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    PUT /identity/users/{userId}/picture

    The request should be of type multipart/form-data. There should be a single file-part included with the binary value of the picture. On top of that, the following additional form-fields can be present:

    mimeType: Optional mime-type for the uploaded picture. If omitted, the default of image/jpeg is used as a mime-type for the picture.

    Body parameter

    string

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    userId path string true No description
    body body BinaryAttachment(binary) true No description

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    204 No Content Indicates the user was found and the picture has been updated. The response-body is left empty intentionally. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested user was not found. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /management/deadletter-jobs

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return job with the given id
    processInstanceId query string false Only return jobs part of a process with the given id
    executionId query string false Only return jobs part of an execution with the given id
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return jobs with the given process definition id
    timersOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are timers. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'messagesOnly'.
    messagesOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are messages. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'timersOnly'
    withException query boolean false If true, only return jobs for which an exception occurred while executing it. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    dueBefore query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed before the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    dueAfter query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed after the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    exceptionMessage query string false Only return jobs with the given exception message
    tenantId query string false Only return jobs with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return jobs with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns jobs without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    locked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are locked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    unlocked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are unlocked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort dueDate
    sort executionId
    sort processInstanceId
    sort retries
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "8",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/management/jobs/8",
      "processInstanceId": "5",
      "processInstanceUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/process-instances/5",
      "processDefinitionId": "timerProcess:1:4",
      "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/timerProcess%3A1%3A4",
      "executionId": "7",
      "executionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/executions/7",
      "retries": 3,
      "exceptionMessage": "null",
      "dueDate": "2013-06-04T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "createTime": "2013-06-03T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "tenantId": "null"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the requested jobs were returned. DataResponseJobResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates an illegal value has been used in a url query parameter or the both 'messagesOnly' and 'timersOnly' are used as parameters. Status description contains additional details about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /management/jobs

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return job with the given id
    processInstanceId query string false Only return jobs part of a process with the given id
    executionId query string false Only return jobs part of an execution with the given id
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return jobs with the given process definition id
    timersOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are timers. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'messagesOnly'.
    messagesOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are messages. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'timersOnly'
    withException query boolean false If true, only return jobs for which an exception occurred while executing it. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    dueBefore query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed before the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    dueAfter query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed after the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    exceptionMessage query string false Only return jobs with the given exception message
    tenantId query string false Only return jobs with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return jobs with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns jobs without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    locked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are locked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    unlocked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are unlocked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort dueDate
    sort executionId
    sort processInstanceId
    sort retries
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "8",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/management/jobs/8",
      "processInstanceId": "5",
      "processInstanceUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/process-instances/5",
      "processDefinitionId": "timerProcess:1:4",
      "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/timerProcess%3A1%3A4",
      "executionId": "7",
      "executionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/executions/7",
      "retries": 3,
      "exceptionMessage": "null",
      "dueDate": "2013-06-04T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "createTime": "2013-06-03T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "tenantId": "null"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the requested jobs were returned. DataResponseJobResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates an illegal value has been used in a url query parameter or the both 'messagesOnly' and 'timersOnly' are used as parameters. Status description contains additional details about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /management/timer-jobs

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return job with the given id
    processInstanceId query string false Only return jobs part of a process with the given id
    executionId query string false Only return jobs part of an execution with the given id
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return jobs with the given process definition id
    timersOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are timers. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'messagesOnly'.
    messagesOnly query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are messages. If false, this parameter is ignored. Cannot be used together with 'timersOnly'
    withException query boolean false If true, only return jobs for which an exception occurred while executing it. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    dueBefore query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed before the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    dueAfter query string(date-time) false Only return jobs which are due to be executed after the given date. Jobs without duedate are never returned using this parameter.
    exceptionMessage query string false Only return jobs with the given exception message
    tenantId query string false Only return jobs with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return jobs with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns jobs without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    locked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are locked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    unlocked query boolean false If true, only return jobs which are unlocked. If false, this parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort dueDate
    sort executionId
    sort processInstanceId
    sort retries
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "8",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/management/jobs/8",
      "processInstanceId": "5",
      "processInstanceUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/process-instances/5",
      "processDefinitionId": "timerProcess:1:4",
      "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/timerProcess%3A1%3A4",
      "executionId": "7",
      "executionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/executions/7",
      "retries": 3,
      "exceptionMessage": "null",
      "dueDate": "2013-06-04T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "createTime": "2013-06-03T22:05:05.474+0000",
      "tenantId": "null"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the requested jobs were returned. DataResponseJobResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates an illegal value has been used in a url query parameter or the both 'messagesOnly' and 'timersOnly' are used as parameters. Status description contains additional details about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /management/tables/{tableName}/data

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    tableName path string true No description
    start query integer false Index of the first row to fetch. Defaults to 0.
    size query integer false Number of rows to fetch, starting from start. Defaults to 10.
    orderAscendingColumn query string false Name of the column to sort the resulting rows on, ascending.
    orderDescendingColumn query string false Name of the column to sort the resulting rows on, descending.

    POST /query/executions

    The request body can contain all possible filters that can be used in the List executions URL query. On top of these, it?s possible to provide an array of variables and processInstanceVariables to include in the query, with their format described here.

    The general paging and sorting query-parameters can be used for this URL.

    Body parameter

    {
  "start": 0,
  "size": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "id": "string",
  "activityId": "string",
  "parentId": "string",
  "processInstanceId": "string",
  "processBusinessKey": "string",
  "processDefinitionId": "string",
  "processDefinitionKey": "string",
  "signalEventSubscriptionName": "string",
  "messageEventSubscriptionName": "string",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "operation": "string",
      "value": {},
      "type": "string",
      "variableOperation": "EQUALS"
    }
  ],
  "processInstanceVariables": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "operation": "string",
      "value": {},
      "type": "string",
      "variableOperation": "EQUALS"
    }
  ],
  "tenantId": "string",
  "tenantIdLike": "string",
  "withoutTenantId": true
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    body body ExecutionQueryRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "5",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/executions/5",

      "activityId": "null",
      "tenantId": "null"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0

    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    POST /query/historic-process-instances

    All supported JSON parameter fields allowed are exactly the same as the parameters found for getting a collection of historic process instances, but passed in as JSON-body arguments rather than URL-parameters to allow for more advanced querying and preventing errors with request-uri?s that are too long. On top of that, the query allows for filtering based on process variables. The variables property is a JSON-array containing objects with the format as described here.

    Body parameter

    {
  "start": 0,
  "size": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "processInstanceId": "string",
  "processInstanceIds": [
    "string"
  ],
  "processBusinessKey": "string",
  "processDefinitionId": "string",
  "processDefinitionKey": "string",
  "superProcessInstanceId": "string",
  "excludeSubprocesses": true,
  "finished": true,
  "involvedUser": "string",
  "finishedAfter": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "finishedBefore": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "startedAfter": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "startedBefore": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "startedBy": "string",
  "includeProcessVariables": true,
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "operation": "string",
      "value": {},
      "type": "string",
      "variableOperation": "EQUALS"
    }
  ],
  "tenantId": "string",
  "tenantIdLike": "string",
  "withoutTenantId": true
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    body body HistoricProcessInstanceQueryRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {

    POST /query/historic-task-instances

    All supported JSON parameter fields allowed are exactly the same as the parameters found for getting a collection of historic task instances, but passed in as JSON-body arguments rather than URL-parameters to allow for more advanced querying and preventing errors with request-uri?s that are too long. On top of that, the query allows for filtering based on process variables. The taskVariables and processVariables properties are JSON-arrays containing objects with the format as described here.

    GET /repository/deployments

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    name query string false Only return deployments with the given name.
    nameLike query string false Only return deployments with a name like the given name.
    category query string false Only return deployments with the given category.
    categoryNotEquals query string false Only return deployments which don?t have the given category.
    tenantId query string false Only return deployments with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return deployments with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns deployments without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort name
    sort deployTime
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [

    POST /repository/deployments

    The request body should contain data of type multipart/form-data. There should be exactly one file in the request, any additional files will be ignored. The deployment name is the name of the file-field passed in. If multiple resources need to be deployed in a single deployment, compress the resources in a zip and make sure the file-name ends with .bar or .zip.

    An additional parameter (form-field) can be passed in the request body with name tenantId. The value of this field will be used as the id of the tenant this deployment is done in.

    Body parameter

    string

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    deploymentKey query string false No description
    deploymentName query string false No description
    tenantId query string false No description
    body body BinaryAttachment(binary) true No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "10",
  "name": "flowable-examples.bar",
  "deploymentTime": "2010-10-13T14:54:26.750+02:00",
  "category": "examples",
  "url": "http://localhost:8081/flowable-rest/service/repository/deployments/10",
  "tenantId": "string"
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK successful operation DeploymentResponse
    201 Created Indicates the deployment was created. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates there was no content present in the request body or the content mime-type is not supported for deployment. The status-description contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /repository/deployments/{deploymentId}/resourcedata/{resourceName}

    The response body will contain the binary resource-content for the requested resource. The response content-type will be the same as the type returned in the resources mimeType property. Also, a content-disposition header is set, allowing browsers to download the file instead of displaying it.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    deploymentId path string true No description
    resourceName path string true The name of the resource to get. Make sure you URL-encode the resourceName in case it contains forward slashes. Eg: use diagrams%2Fmy-process.bpmn20.xml instead of diagrams/my-process.bpmn20.xml.

    Example responses

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates both deployment and resource have been found and the resource data has been returned. Inline
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested deployment was not found or there is no resource with the given id present in the deployment. The status-description contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return models with the given version.
    category query string false Only return models with the given category.
    categoryLike query string false Only return models with a category like the given name.
    categoryNotEquals query string false Only return models which don?t have the given category.
    name query string false Only return models with the given name.
    nameLike query string false Only return models with a name like the given name.
    key query string false Only return models with the given key.
    deploymentId query string false Only return models with the given category.
    version query integer false Only return models with the given version.
    latestVersion query boolean false If true, only return models which are the latest version. Best used in combination with key. If false is passed in as value, this is ignored and all versions are returned.
    deployed query boolean false If true, only deployed models are returned. If false, only undeployed models are returned (deploymentId is null).
    tenantId query string false Only return models with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return models with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns models without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort category
    sort createTime
    sort key
    sort lastUpdateTime
    sort name
    sort version
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "name": "Model name",
      "key": "Model key",
      "category": "Model category",
      "version": 2,
      "metaInfo": "Model metainfo",
      "deploymentId": "7",
      "tenantId": "null",
      "id": "5",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/models/5",
      "createTime": "2013-06-12T12:31:19.861+0000",
      "lastUpdateTime": "2013-06-12T12:31:19.861+0000",
      "deploymentUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/deployments/2",
      "sourceUrl": "string",
      "sourceExtraUrl": "string"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates request was successful and the models are returned DataResponseModelResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates a parameter was passed in the wrong format. The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /repository/process-definitions

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    version query integer false Only return process definitions with the given version.
    name query string false Only return process definitions with the given name.
    nameLike query string false Only return process definitions with a name like the given name.
    key query string false Only return process definitions with the given key.
    keyLike query string false Only return process definitions with a name like the given key.
    resourceName query string false Only return process definitions with the given resource name.
    resourceNameLike query string false Only return process definitions with a name like the given resource name.
    category query string false Only return process definitions with the given category.
    categoryLike query string false Only return process definitions with a category like the given name.
    categoryNotEquals query string false Only return process definitions which don?t have the given category.
    deploymentId query string false Only return process definitions with the given category.
    startableByUser query string false Only return process definitions which are part of a deployment with the given id.
    latest query boolean false Only return the latest process definition versions. Can only be used together with key and keyLike parameters, using any other parameter will result in a 400-response.
    suspended query boolean false If true, only returns process definitions which are suspended. If false, only active process definitions (which are not suspended) are returned.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort name
    sort id
    sort key
    sort category
    sort deploymentId
    sort version

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "oneTaskProcess:1:4",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/oneTaskProcess%3A1%3A4",
      "key": "oneTaskProcess",
      "version": 1,
      "name": "The One Task Process",
      "description": "This is a process for testing purposes",
      "tenantId": "null",
      "deploymentId": "2",
      "deploymentUrl": "http://localhost:8081/repository/deployments/2",
      "resource": "http://localhost:8182/repository/deployments/2/resources/testProcess.xml",
      "diagramResource": "http://localhost:8182/repository/deployments/2/resources/testProcess.png",
      "category": "Examples",
      "graphicalNotationDefined": true,
      "suspended": true,
      "startFormDefined": true
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates request was successful and the process-definitions are returned DataResponseProcessDefinitionResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates a parameter was passed in the wrong format or that latest is used with other parameters other than key and keyLike. The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    PUT /repository/process-definitions/{processDefinitionId}

    Execute actions for a process definition (Update category, Suspend or Activate)

    Body parameter

    {
  "action": "activate",
  "includeProcessInstances": true,
  "date": "2017-11-21T09:05:13Z",
  "category": "string"
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    processDefinitionId path string true No description
    body body ProcessDefinitionActionRequest true No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "oneTaskProcess:1:4",
  "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/oneTaskProcess%3A1%3A4",
  "key": "oneTaskProcess",
  "version": 1,
  "name": "The One Task Process",
  "description": "This is a process for testing purposes",
  "tenantId": "null",
  "deploymentId": "2",
  "deploymentUrl": "http://localhost:8081/repository/deployments/2",
  "resource": "http://localhost:8182/repository/deployments/2/resources/testProcess.xml",
  "diagramResource": "http://localhost:8182/repository/deployments/2/resources/testProcess.png",
  "category": "Examples",
  "graphicalNotationDefined": true,
  "suspended": true,
  "startFormDefined": true
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates action has been executed for the specified process. (category altered, activate or suspend) ProcessDefinitionResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates no category was defined in the request body. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested process definition was not found. None
    409 Conflict Indicates the requested process definition is already suspended or active. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    404 Not Found Indicates the requested process definition was not found or the process definition doesn?t have an identity-link that matches the url. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /runtime/event-subscriptions

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given id
    eventType query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given event type
    eventName query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given event name
    activityId query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given activity id
    executionId query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given execution id
    processInstanceId query string false Only return event subscriptions part of a process with the given id
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given process definition id
    createdBefore query string(date-time) false Only return event subscriptions which are created before the given date.
    createdAfter query string(date-time) false Only return event subscriptions which are created after the given date.
    tenantId query string false Only return event subscriptions with the given tenant id.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort created
    sort executionId
    sort processInstanceId
    sort processDefinitionId
    sort tenantId

    GET /runtime/executions

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return models with the given version.
    activityId query string false Only return executions with the given activity id.
    processDefinitionKey query string false Only return process instances with the given process definition key.
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return process instances with the given process definition id.
    processInstanceId query string false Only return executions which are part of the process instance with the given id.
    messageEventSubscriptionName query string false Only return executions which are subscribed to a message with the given name.
    signalEventSubscriptionName query string false Only return executions which are subscribed to a signal with the given name.
    parentId query string false Only return executions which are a direct child of the given execution.
    tenantId query string false Only return process instances with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return process instances with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns process instances without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort processInstanceId
    sort processDefinitionId
    sort processDefinitionKey
    sort tenantId

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "5",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/executions/5",
      "parentId": "null",
      "parentUrl": "null",
      "superExecutionId": "null",
      "superExecutionUrl": "null",
      "processInstanceId": "5",
      "processInstanceUrl": "http://localhost:8182/runtime/process-instances/5",
      "suspended": true,
      "activityId": "null",
      "tenantId": "null"
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates request was successful and the executions are returned DataResponseExecutionResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates a parameter was passed in the wrong format . The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the execution was found and the action is performed. ExecutionResponse
    204 No Content Indicates the execution was found, the action was performed and the action caused the execution to end. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates an illegal action was requested, required parameters are missing in the request body or illegal variables are passed in. Status description contains additional information about the error. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the execution was not found. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    POST /runtime/executions/{executionId}/variables

    This endpoint can be used in 2 ways: By passing a JSON Body (array of RestVariable) or by passing a multipart/form-data Object. Any number of variables can be passed into the request body array.

    Body parameter

    {
  "name": "myVariable",
  "type": "string",
  "value": "test",
  "valueUrl": "http://....",
  "scope": "string"
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    executionId path string true No description
    body body RestVariable false Update a task variable

    Example responses

    {}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK successful operation object
    201 Created Indicates the execution was found and variable is created/updated. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates the request body is incomplete or contains illegal values. The status description contains additional information about the error. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested execution was not found. None
    409 Conflict Indicates the execution was found but already contains a variable with the given name. Use the update-method instead. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates both the execution and variable were found and variable is returned. RestVariable
    400 Bad Request Indicates the request body is incomplete or contains illegal values. The status description contains additional information about the error. None
    404 Not Found Indicates the requested execution was not found or the execution does not have a variable with the given name in the requested scope (in case scope-query parameter was omitted, variable doesn?t exist in local and global scope). Status description contains additional information about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /runtime/process-instances

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    id query string false Only return models with the given version.
    processDefinitionKey query string false Only return process instances with the given process definition key.
    processDefinitionId query string false Only return process instances with the given process definition id.
    businessKey query string false Only return process instances with the given businessKey.
    involvedUser query string false Only return process instances in which the given user is involved.
    suspended query boolean false If true, only return process instance which are suspended. If false, only return process instances which are not suspended (active).
    superProcessInstanceId query string false Only return process instances which have the given super process-instance id (for processes that have a call-activities).
    subProcessInstanceId query string false Only return process instances which have the given sub process-instance id (for processes started as a call-activity).
    excludeSubprocesses query boolean false Return only process instances which aren?t sub processes.
    includeProcessVariables query boolean false Indication to include process variables in the result.
    tenantId query string false Only return process instances with the given tenantId.
    tenantIdLike query string false Only return process instances with a tenantId like the given value.
    withoutTenantId query boolean false If true, only returns process instances without a tenantId set. If false, the withoutTenantId parameter is ignored.
    sort query string false Property to sort on, to be used together with the order.

    Enumerated Values

    Parameter Value
    sort id
    sort processDefinitionId
    sort tenantId
    sort processDefinitionKey

    Example responses

    {
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "187",
      "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
      "businessKey": "myBusinessKey",
      "suspended": true,
      "ended": true,
      "processDefinitionId": "oneTaskProcess:1:158",
      "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
      "activityId": "processTask",
      "variables": [
        {
          "name": "myVariable",
          "type": "string",
          "value": "test",
          "valueUrl": "http://....",
          "scope": "string"
        }
      ],
      "tenantId": "null",
      "completed": true
    }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "start": 0,
  "sort": "string",
  "order": "string",
  "size": 0
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates request was successful and the process-instances are returned DataResponseProcessInstanceResponse
    400 Bad Request Indicates a parameter was passed in the wrong format . The status-message contains additional information. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    POST /runtime/process-instances

    Note that also a transientVariables property is accepted as part of this json, that follows the same structure as the variables property.

    Only one of processDefinitionId, processDefinitionKey or message can be used in the request body.

    Parameters businessKey, variables and tenantId are optional.

    If tenantId is omitted, the default tenant will be used. More information about the variable format can be found in the REST variables section.

    Note that the variable-scope that is supplied is ignored, process-variables are always local.

    Body parameter

    {
  "processDefinitionId": "oneTaskProcess:1:158",
  "processDefinitionKey": "oneTaskProcess",
  "message": "newOrderMessage",
  "businessKey": "myBusinessKey",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "myVariable",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "test",
      "valueUrl": "http://....",
      "scope": "string"
    }
  ],
  "transientVariables": [
    {
      "name": "myVariable",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "test",
      "valueUrl": "http://....",
      "scope": "string"
    }
  ],
  "tenantId": "tenant1",
  "returnVariables": true
}

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    body body ProcessInstanceCreateRequest false No description

    Example responses

    {
  "id": "187",
  "url": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
  "businessKey": "myBusinessKey",
  "suspended": true,
  "ended": true,
  "processDefinitionId": "oneTaskProcess:1:158",
  "processDefinitionUrl": "http://localhost:8182/repository/process-definitions/processOne%3A1%3A4",
  "activityId": "processTask",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "myVariable",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "test",
      "valueUrl": "http://....",
      "scope": "string"
    }
  ],
  "tenantId": "null",
  "completed": true
}

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK successful operation ProcessInstanceResponse
    201 Created Indicates the process instance was created. None
    400 Bad Request Indicates either the process-definition was not found (based on id or key), no process is started by sending the given message or an invalid variable has been passed. Status description contains additional information about the error. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.

    GET /runtime/process-instances/{processInstanceId}/variables

    In case the variable is a binary variable or serializable, the valueUrl points to an URL to fetch the raw value. If it?s a plain variable, the value is present in the response. Note that only local scoped variables are returned, as there is no global scope for process-instance variables.

    Parameters

    Parameter In Type Required Description
    processInstanceId path string true No description
    scope query string false No description

    Example responses

    [
  {
    "name": "myVariable",
    "type": "string",
    "value": "test",
    "valueUrl": "http://....",
    "scope": "string"
  }
]

    Responses

    Status Meaning Description Schema
    200 OK Indicates the process instance was found and variables are returned. Inline
    400 Bad Request Indicates the requested process instance was not found. None
    To perform this operation, you must be authenticated.
